Genes

Rigel

November 1, 2017

The data set Genes contains a single response Y (whether the leaf length for a particular plant was bigger than average) and p = 3,235 genetic markers. . If Y = 1, then the leaf length is greater than average for that plant and Y = 0 otherwise. . The genetic markers are coded as 1, 0.5, 0. A higher value suggests that the gene is more switched on. You may treat these as continuous variables.

The Question? . Determine which, if any, of the genetic markers are associated with with a greater than average leaf length.

library(readxl)
genes<- read_excel("C:/Users/Rigel/Desktop/Final Semester/STAT learning individual Assignment/Genes_Data_converted.xlsx")
